The Anambra State Police Command has confirmed the death of two notorious armed robbery suspects, one Onyebuchi Ngala ‘m’ aka Ceaser and Izuchukwu Okoro ‘m’, who has been terrorising Awka city and its environs after a gun battle. The Command’s PPRO, SP Mohammed Haruna, who confirmed the death via a statement he issued to journalist on Monday evening in Awka, said, at about 1:15 pm, January 13th, 2020, that Police operatives attached to the Command Special Anti Robbery Squad (SARS) responded to a distress call and stormed the hideout of a robbery gang who allegedly attacked one Chiegulem Chidera ‘m’ at Agouye Umuko Awka and snatched his Nissan Xterra jeep with Reg number Cross River GGJ 402 AA at gunpoint. ALSO READ: 20,621 arrested  for seat belt violation in Anambra ― FRSC 20,621 arrested  for seat belt violation in Anambra ― FRSC Police arrested 275 suspected criminals in Kwara in 2019’ One collapses, as fire razes Onitsha spare parts market There must be consequences for bad behaviour during… According to Mohammed, the suspects were trailed at Nkwo Agulu and on sighting the Police opened fire after which the police responded promptly, as a result, the two suspects one Onyebuchi Ngala ‘m’ aka Ceaser and Izuchukwu Okoro ‘m’ were fatally wounded during the gun encounter. And they were taken to the hospital for treatment but confirmed dead on arrival by the medical doctor. “Exhibits recovered from the suspects include the snatched Xterra jeep, one Ak 47 rifle, one pump action gun, six life cartridges, four expended ammunition, five life ammunition of 7.62mm and two Ak47 magazines. He noted that the deceased suspects were also among the gang responsible for the Abduction of one Engr Emeka Chiaghana ‘m’ of Nibo on 25/10/2019. “Meanwhile, the case is still under investigation and effort is ongoing to locate the whereabouts of the abducted victim. STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLIC